ers were deadly and I started feeling sick and very hot,\\\" he said in an interview after the race had ended.\", \"from\": 1527, \"to\": 1655, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The last four kilometers\", \"from\": 1527, \"to\": 1551}, {\"ngram\": \"an interview\", \"from\": 1617, \"to\": 1629}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 1636, \"to\": 1644}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speculation followed soon after, with many pointing fingers at the status of the river as the culprit.\", \"from\": 1657, \"to\": 1759, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Speculation\", \"from\": 1657, \"to\": 1668}, {\"ngram\": \"many pointing fingers\", \"from\": 1695, \"to\": 1716}, {\"ngram\": \"the status\", \"from\": 1720, \"to\": 1730}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 1734, \"to\": 1743}, {\"ngram\": \"the culprit\", \"from\": 1747, \"to\": 1758}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Mislawshuck himself put an end to the speculation in an interview with theCanadian Presson August 1, 2024.\", \"from\": 1760, \"to\": 1870, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Mislawshuck\", \"from\": 1764, \"to\": 1775}, {\"ngram\": \"an end\", \"from\": 1788, \"to\": 1794}, {\"ngram\": \"the speculation\", \"from\": 1798, \"to\": 1813}, {\"ngram\": \"an interview\", \"from\": 1817, \"to\": 1829}, {\"ngram\": \"theCanadian Presson August\", \"from\": 1835, \"to\": 1861}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was coming back from an Achilles tear,\\\" he explained, adding that he wanted to push himself as far as he could because he felt it was his last chance.\", \"from\": 1872, \"to\": 2025, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1899, \"end\": 1907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Achilles_tendon\", \"score\": 0.6556757838020129, \"rank\": 0.5251440188948384, \"text\": \"Achilles\", \"types\": [\"Q4936952\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Achilles_tendon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Achilles_tendon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his last chance\", \"from